column24: 'Psychiatry cannot be fully defined if psychotherapies are outruled. Moreover psychoanalysis  carry the very foundations of psychiatry.   Psychodynamic oriented psychotherapies provide a way to a deeper understanding of our patients and their profound change regarding patterns of beliefs

column70: 'In Greece by the term psychiatric training in public hospitals
column71: we only mean pharmaceutical treatments and no psychotherapy. Most of our psychiatrists-supervisors are not trained in psychotherapy and you can only pay on your own in private institutions to get a psychotherapy training... Moreover if you want to treat your patients using psychotherapeutic technics you can do so on your free time extra from your usual psychiatric appointment and probono...:('
